Metadata-Version: 2.1
Name: tartufo
Version: 0.0.1
Summary: tartufo is a tool for scanning git repositories for secrets/passwords/high-entropy data
Home-page: https://github.com/godaddy/tartufo
Author: GoDaddy
Author-email: oss@godaddy.com
License: GNU
Download-URL: https://pypi.org/project/tartufo/#files
Description: Seaches for secrets/high-entropy/passwords in git histories and pre-commit blobs with the intent to provide developers a way of preventing accidental leaking of privileged data. This project was inspired by Dylan Ayrey's project truffleHog https://github.com/dxa4481/truffleHog
